message: /* Important destinations served by trains from the Gare de l'Est */

Zürich (first), Basel (second) and Geneva (third) are the three major economic centres of the country, Lugano is most certainly not. Basel is the capital of the pharmaceutical industry of the country which accounts for half of all Swiss exports to the world. It is also home to the most important financial institute of the world (BIS) and by the way: Basel airport is where Swiss International Airlines is domiciled and the airport has been founded and is owned/financed by the Swiss government.

It makes much more sense to speak of the three major economic centres of the country, where the majority of the international organisations (Geneva and Basel) and the only three Swiss international airports are located. There is no need to talk about the obscure category of ''global cities''.

page: School for Advanced Studies in the Social Sciences

message: It makes much more sense to include Basel as well, since it's the second largest economic centre of the country, has the third and last international airport of Switzerland and through the Bank for International Settlements is home to one of the most important international organisatios in the world.

/* Other institutions of the higher education sector */

This list is primarily related to the Swiss definition of "universities" as publicly-funded institutions. That definition excludes other entities that are not eligible for public financing, but are accredited and legally allowed to use the term "university".  Since this list excludes those other entities, this entry needs to be clear that the list is only about publicly-funded universities, not all universities in Switzerland.
